FBIS4-37013 "drnes116_j_94019" FBIS-NES-94-116 Daily Report 16 Jun 1994 ARABIAN PENINSULA Yemen At Least 18 Reportedly Killed in Aden Shelling At Least 18 Reportedly Killed in Aden Shelling NC1606071694 Paris AFP in English 0607 GMT 16 Jun 94 NC1606071694 Paris AFP English BFN [Text] Aden, Yemen, June 16 (AFP)--Northern shelling killed at least 18 people early Thursday in a suburb of the southern stronghold of Aden, hospital officials said. The shelling also set fire to several homes in the Shaykh 'Uthman suburb, just to the north of the city, and sent residents fleeing to safer areas. The wounded were still being taken to the Al-Jumhuriyah hospital three hours after the dawn attack, officials at the hospital added. Shaykh 'Uthman is about 10 kilometers (six miles) from the front lines to the north where southern and northern forces have been fighting artillery duels almost daily. The war in Yemen broke out on May 5.
